# ORIG TITLE    Portuguese transport workers to strike over budget and pay cuts . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Staff at Portugal’s national airline TAP will stage a strike from March 21-23 in protest over the budget, pay and job cuts. Following massive rallies in Lisbon and dozens of other cities on Saturday to demand the austerity-minded government’s resignation, a railroad workers’ strike against pay cuts is also planned for next Wednesday and Thursday. 
